<article>
    <h1>Get re&#xAD;trench&#xAD;ment-re&#xAD;lated info on re&#xAD;vamped app</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200920/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-20"><time>2020-09-20</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | FEATURES</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Job seek­ers who want bite-sized in­for­ma­tion to help them make in­formed ca­reer de­ci­sions can turn to a re­vamped gov­ern­ment smart­phone app, LifeSG, which was up­graded last month.</p>
    <p>Pre­vi­ously known as Mo­ments of Life, the app now fea­tures a se­ries of em­ploy­ment sup­port guides, pro­vid­ing in­for­ma­tion on top­ics such as re­trench­ment ben­e­fits and mea­sures.</p>
    <p>One guide, for ex­am­ple, aims to help the re­trenched nav­i­gate var­i­ous op­tions and as­sis­tance pro­grammes avail­able to them, such as ap­proach­ing statu­tory board Work­force Sin­ga­pore (WSG) for ca­reer coach­ing and help in look­ing for a new job.</p>
    <p>The guide also pro­vides in­for­ma­tion re­lated to no­tice pe­ri­ods, re­trench­ment ben­e­fits and al­ter­na­tives to re­trench­ment.</p>
    <p>The em­ploy­ment sup­port guides are launched by the Min­istry of Man­power, WSG and Gov­ern­ment Tech­nol­ogy Agency, and sup­ported by Skill­sFu­ture Sin­ga­pore, the Em­ploy­ment and Em­ploy­a­bil­ity In­sti­tute, Tri­par­tite Al­liance for Fair & Pro­gres­sive Em­ploy­ment Prac­tices and Tri­par­tite Al­liance for Dis­pute Man­age­ment.</p>
    <p>Through the LifeSG app, users can also access other gov­ern­ment services such as check­ing their Cen­tral Prov­i­dent Fund (CPF) bal­ances, ap­ply­ing for HDB sea­son park­ing and ap­ply­ing for a pass­port.</p>

